name: MULA SEM CABEÇA - Xylography #04
description:
Mula sem Cabeça ("Headless Mule") is a legend present in some Latin American countries, including Brazil, where it is very popular. 
In the northeast it was common to hear from the elderly stories of people who had seen this animal that, according to the myth, were cursed women.
Digital art inspired by Xylographs and cordel from the Brazilian northeast.
